OL,3,CRetired police chief who plotted to
OL,4,Cattack ex-wife jailed for 6 years
OL,6,FProsecutor Miles Trigg said that
OL,7,FHorne's intentions were evidenced by
OL,8,Fhis behaviour both at the property and
OL,9,Fthe notes on his phone. These notes
OL,10,Fwere intending something that at least
OL,11,Famounted to grievous bodily harm, the
OL,12,Fprosecutor said.
OL,14,FMr Trigg described Horne's extensive
OL,15,Fplanning - noting that he had been
OL,16,Fshopping for a Stanley Knife and duct
OL,17,Ftape; chose to park at a distance;
OL,18,Fcamped overnight at an outhouse; cut
OL,19,Fpieces of rope for tying up Ms Heyes
OL,20,Fand he was carrying two blades when
OL,21,Fthe offence of burglary was committed.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/15
